{"change_summary":"Fixed both pending milestone-record amendments. `latest_task_runs_per_bead` now treats equal `started_at` values as an append-order tie so a later same-timestamp retry stays authoritative, and `find_matching_running_task_run` now reuses a sole runless running attempt even when the retry arrives with a different `started_at`, allowing legacy `run_id=None` start retries to repair partial lineage/snapshot writes after a journal failure. Added model and service regressions covering same-timestamp retry snapshot state and runless start-retry recovery.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage.","Legacy attempts that still omit `run_id` remain inherently ambiguous for completion updates when multiple same-project attempts are open at once; this round improves single-open retry recovery but does not make multi-open legacy finalization deterministic."],"steps":[{"description":"Adjusted task-run recency selection in `model.rs` so same-timestamp retries break ties by later slice order instead of preferring an older terminal row, which keeps snapshot reconciliation aligned with the newest attempt for each bead.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Broadened runless running-attempt matching so a sole legacy open row can be reused for a retry repair even when the retried start call has a different `started_at`, avoiding the unrecoverable `already active` path after a start-side journal failure.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Added regressions in `model.rs` and `service.rs` for same-timestamp retry recency, runless retry matching, snapshot reconciliation after a same-timestamp retry, and `run_id=None` start retry repair after a simulated journal failure.","order":2,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Reformatted the workspace and revalidated the milestone-record path with unit tests and clippy.","order":3,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 98 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}